caption: One of the most delicious meals I’ve had in a while! We came for the brunch, we all had something different, and everyone finished their plate. Service was impeccable and food arrived looking perfect and tasting delicious. Def recommend!

I live really close to Casa Ora and it's always the first option that comes to my mind when someone is looking for a relaxed place with incredible food. I remember we came here Christmas eve 2020 and they made us feel so welcomed and their drinks were so great we ended up ordering so much. Their empanadas are the best and I can't wait to see what they have in store for Summer 2021!
We absolutely love everything about Casa Ora. Not one bone to pick. The staff, the food, the drinks. Highly recommend. point blank period.
I had a great time! The vibes are on point. Will be back soon :)

This is my neighborhood go to spot. Seriously feels like home, with incredible food, hospitality, and flavors. I always recommend this spot, it's hidden on a smaller street and the cocktails are unlike any others.
The staff is so friendly and the food can't be beat. I appreciate their safety precautions in the pandemic to make for a safe and truly hospitable dining experience!
Great food and drinks! A few good vegan options and wonderful staff. A gem in the area.

My girlfriends and I went here for the first time a few weeks ago and we loved it! The drinks are amazing and the atmosphere is perfect too. Highly recommend for a girls night, first day, or even date night. I got the put the lime in the coconut cocktail - felt like I was at the beach!

Me and my roommates had the most amazing experience here. We came just for drinks and our waiter was so nice. The atmosphere is great! I highly recommend asking for seating in the library. It’s very intimate and a great spot for future date nights :)
The best place to get cocktails and the staff are so friendly. I’m so happy that they also offer vegan options that are both delicious and filling.

Really love this place - the drinks are unique and delicious and the food is amazing - def have to get the guac and plantain chips. Not a TON of vegetarian options but the food is really amazing. great atmosphere and overall vibe.

In this neighborhood if I know I wanna go somewhere a little special I stop by here. Everyone is incredibly friendly, the service is excellent, the food is fresh and hot, good atmosphere, and the drinks are inventive and tasty. Casa Ora is a truly great place.
awfully overpriced. enjoyed the drinks, but not enough to make me come back.

WOW WOW WOW, I've haven't had food like this in a long time. Definitely amazing!!! The price makes up for the taste, quality & size. Feels like comfort food. Will be coming back

I vowed not to write a review until a restaurant truly deserved it. Tonight I am saddened to say, Casa Ora and it’s future patrons deserve to know the tragedy that was my experience.  It started off with exceptional cocktails. Well crafted and timely delivered....  Then, as the night got cooler the experience fell off terribly. First, as we asked them to turn heaters up. Three different individuals came by to make different bs excuses - including, my favorite, “we would get fined if we made it warmer.”  We were “offered” a wait inside for inside seats at 25% capacity.  However, when we peered inside it was packed wall-to-wall with people. If that’s 25% capacity, I can’t imagine what a full house is like.  Out of courtesy and consideration for the hardship the restaurant may be in, we decided to wait.  Long story short, we waited more than an hour and a half for food - the kind servers continuously insisting it would “only be 5 minutes longer.”  Once our food arrived, it was mediocre at best. The scallops were good but the Pabellon was VERY dry and overcooked.  They tried their best to comp us with a drink but the experience was unacceptable.  When we brought issue with the bill, the owner brushed us off.  We got to dinner at 8:15 and left at 11:30 exhausted, offended, and appalled.
Positively delicious!

I am originally from Venezuela , and I have to say The food and the flavor was on point but the size of the dishes and the prices don’t match.  I think they are over charging and for that reason I would not recommend this place.

This was one of the best restaurant experiences I have had in nyc. The food was excellent and each dish was well thought out in terms of flavor and consistency (there is not another place like this currently in any of the 5 boroughs). The drinks were also extremely impressive. The service was very good. I never had a plate sitting on my table after I finished for more than 5 minutes. I highly recommend this restaurant and wish they would open on the upper east side because if they did I would be there twice a week.

I understand that people tip under 20 percent but it’s not very pleasant to see the high prices on the menu plus the note of the gratuity charge.

We had an amazing, social-distanced indoor dining experience at Casa Ora last weekend. We ordered the mandocas and ceviche to start, followed by octopus and scallops for entrees and the cuatro leches cake for dessert. The scallop entree was the BIGGEST *and* most affordable scallop main I have ever ordered in New York — each scallop was super thick, soft and well cooked. The ceviche and cake in particular were exploding with multiple layers of flavor. Would highly recommend this restaurant to anyone visiting the area! We’ll definitely be back :)

Incredibly cute place across the street from our apartment. For the longest time, we kept putting off going here because we could do it anytime. Finally went there last week and it was INCREDIBLE. They've done an amazing job with their outside with the planters and well-distanced yet adequate seating, fun music. Best of all, the drinks are awesome and food/apps were delicious. Get the tamarind cocktail if they have it. The service from Juan was top-notch with on-point recommendations for all courses. After Winson became a destination restaurant in the neighborhood, didn't think it would be possible to have another. I think Casa Ora has the potential to be the 2nd one! Just hope outdoor dining lasts for a long time or there's another system figured out. P.S. the menus signed by Ora were a nice touch!

Chanced by here with my GF on a warm day, and drawn in by the lovely outdoor seating area and the “frozen margaritas“ on the chalkboard. Everything about this place turned out amazing. Our waitress was Iskra, who was a delight—super friendly, attentive, and really helpful describing the dishes. GF loved the beet salad. I had the short rib, which was braised to perfection. We also had an appetizer, though I forget the name—it was kind of a super thin doughnut served with soft cream along with queso blanco. Truth: this place was worth it for that appetizer alone. Our drinks were all at so really good--ice cold, generous, nice and stiff. Rest of the staff here was super pleasant. Would be back here in a heartbeat.

(Translated by Google) There is a secret formula in life: to dream big things and taste small pleasures !!!! It fits perfectly in this place to know that it is a dream come true of its owner, after several years of constant learning; It is a place with almost purely familiar attention in which they demonstrate with their attention and with their flavors that love overflows in the things they do .... Their theme is Venezuelan food and who can resist some mandras (who had more 3 years without feeling the taste and they tasted the homemade ones in Venezuela) and some tequeños of entry or even some empanadas or some cupcakes !!!! We also ate a delicious cachapa with cheese and cream (they told us that they prepare it themselves) and a patacón (their roasted meat has the family secret because the taste is delicious Omg), and to close with a flourish the dessert was a mousse of parchita and a four milks (whose caramel has been the most delicious of my life), I recommend it 1000%, it is that cozy, familiar and beautiful place, take care of every detail (until your bathroom is simply beautiful) would come back again, what Super recommend.  (Original) Hay una fórmula secreta en la vida: soñar cosas grandes y saborear pequeños placeres!!!! Encaja perfectamente en este lugar al saber que es un sueño hecho realidad de su dueño, luego de varios años de constante aprendizaje; es un lugar con atención casi netamente familiar en el que demuestran con su atención y con sus sabores que el amor desborda en las cosas que hacen.... Su temática es la comida venezolana y quien se puede resistir a unas mandocas (que tenía más de 3 años sin sentir el sabor y sabían a las hechas en casa en Venezuela) y a unos tequeños de entrada o hasta unas empanadas o unos pastelitos!!!! También comimos una deliciosa cachapa con queso y nata (nos contaron que la preparan ellos mismos) y un patacón (su carne mechada tiene el secreto de familia porque el sabor es Omg riquísimo), y para cerrar con broche de oro el postre fue un mousse de parchita y una cuatro leches (cuyo caramelo ha sido el más delicioso de mi vida), lo recomiendo al 1000%, es ese lugar acogedor, familiar y hermoso, cuidan cada detalle ( hasta su baño es simplemente hermoso) volvería de nuevo, lo súper recomiendo.
